The "pointing at a mouse and calling it a duck" incident continues to ferment online
A primary school teacher released a video, using "pointing at a mouse and calling it a duck" to teach children that when faced with mistakes from authority, they must have the courage to resist and have the ability to think independently.
After the video went viral, the author said that he had to delete the video due to some pressure.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Follow-up: CCTV came out to support the school involved
Called the "foreign object" a duck neck, which is normal food.

Real-name system and censorship for AirDrop are here
On June 6, the Cyberspace Administration of China publicly solicited opinions on the "Regulations on the Management of Information Services in Short-range Self-organizing Networks (Draft for Comments)"
Among the requirements: users must provide real identity information, automatic pairing is not allowed, snapshots, thumbnails and other summary information preview functions are not provided by default, and a convenient complaint reporting portal or complaint reporting channel needs to be set up.
